title: India Tariffs Cut To 10% As Donald Trump Faces US Supreme Court Setback
summary_full: US trading partners, including India, that have reached tariff deals with Donald Trump's administration before the Supreme Court verdict, will now face a 10 per cent duty, despite higher levels they may have agreed on previously, the White House said
